org.jcvi.jillion.fasta

Interface FastaParser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BfaParser, FastaFileParser

    public interface FastaParser
    FastaParser is an interface that will parse a FASTA formatted structure and call the appropriate visit methods on the given FastaVisitor.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • canParse

        boolean canParse()
        Can this parser accept new parse requests via parse() calls. Some implementations of FastaParser may only allow one parse call in its lifetime (for example, if the fasta structure is being parsed via an InputStream).
        Returns:
        true if this handler can handle new parse requests; false otherwise.

      • canCreateMemento

        boolean canCreateMemento()
        Is this FastaParser's callbacks capable of creating FastaVisitorCallback.FastaVisitorMementos.
        Returns:
        true if this callback can create mementos; false otherwise.

      • isReadOnceOnly

        boolean isReadOnceOnly()
        Can the parse(FastaVisitor) or #parse(FastaVisitor, FastaVisitorMemento) methods be called multiple times. Some implementations are working off of an InputStream that can't be rewound or reset we can only read Once.
        Returns:
        true if the data can only be parsed once; false otherwise.

      • parse

        void parse(FastaVisitor visitor)
    throws IOException
        Parse the fasta structure starting from the beginning and call the appropriate visit methods on the given FastaVisitor.
        Parameters:
        visitor - the FastaVisitor instance to call visit methods on; can not be null;
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the fasta.
        NullPointerException - if visitor is null.
        IllegalStateException - if this handler can not accept any new parse requests.
        See Also:
        canParse()

      • parse

        void parse(FastaVisitor visitor,
           FastaVisitorCallback.FastaVisitorMemento memento)
    throws IOException
        Parse the fasta structure starting from location provided by the FastaVisitorCallback.FastaVisitorMemento and call the appropriate visit methods on the given FastaVisitor.
        Parameters:
        visitor - the FastaVisitor instance to call visit methods on; can not be null;
        memento - the FastaVisitorCallback.FastaVisitorMemento instance to tell the parser where to start parsing from; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the fasta file.
        NullPointerException - if either the visitor or memento are null.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if mementos are not supported by this parser implementation (for example when parsing an InputStream instead of a File).
        IllegalStateException - if this handler can not accept any new parse requests.
        See Also:
        canParse()
